  "justification": "This function implements the exact three-way merge algorithm described. It takes three ICompareResult objects (localToRemote, baseToLocal, baseToRemote) and returns an object with four sets: added, removed, updated, and conflicts. The implementation iterates through keys removed/added/updated in local and remote versions, detecting conflicts when both sides diverge. It specifically: (1) checks if keys removed locally were updated in remote (marks as conflicts), (2) checks if keys removed remotely were updated locally (marks as conflicts, else removes), (3) checks if keys added locally were also added in remote with different values (marks as conflicts), (4) checks if keys added remotely were also added locally with different values (marks as conflicts, else adds), (5) checks if keys updated locally were also updated remotely with different values (marks as conflicts), (6) checks if keys updated remotely were also updated locally with different values (marks as conflicts, else updates), and (7) already-conflicted keys are skipped via guards to avoid duplicate processing. This function is part of the Settings Sync infrastructure used for reconciling keybindings across local and remote during synchronization."
}

